<HEADLINE> Medical Chopper Crashes; Three Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRESNO, Texas (AP) -- A Life Flight medical helicopter crashed  
into a field southwest of Houston on Saturday, killing three people 
aboard. 
</P>
<P>
	Texas Department of Public Safety spokesman Tom Vinger said the  
chopper went down about 12:45 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	The dead were a pilot, a nurse and one other crew member, Vinger  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Life Flight chopper was going from Houston's Hermann  
Hospital to pick up a patient. 
</P>
<P>
	Vinger said the helicopter apparently had problems before the  
crash. 
</P>
<P>
	``Witnesses reported they heard an explosion,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	The crash site is about 40 miles south of Houston.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
