<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Names Keys New Delhi News Editor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Laurinda Keys, who has reported for The  
Associated Press from Europe, South Africa and Asia, has been named 
news editor in New Delhi. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Friday by AP President Louis D.  
Boccardi. 
</P>
<P>
	Keys began her AP career in 1976 as a newswoman in Los Angeles.  
In 1982 she was named supervisory correspondent in San Diego. Two 
years later she was transferred to the International Desk and in 
1986 was assigned to Johannesburg as a correspondent. She was 
appointed news editor in Stockholm in 1990 and in Frankfurt in 
1994. Three years later she was assigned to Singapore. 
</P>
<P>
	Keys, 48, is a native of Los Angeles and a graduate of the  
University of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
	She succeeds Donna Bryson, who has been named chief Middle East  
correspondent based in Cairo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
