<HEADLINE>  Facts About JFK Jr.'s Plane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Facts and figures about the Piper Saratoga II HP, the type of  
airplane carrying John F. Kennedy Jr. and two others Friday night 
when it disappeared en route from Fairfield, N.J., to Martha's 
Vineyard, Mass.: 

</P>
<P>
	Manufacturer: The New Piper Aircraft, Inc., a Vero Beach,  
Fla.-based company known for its line of personal aircraft and 
business models. 
</P>
<P>
	Seating: Six.  
</P>
<P>
	Maximum speed: 175 knots, or about 201 mph.  
</P>
<P>
	Cruising range: 859 nautical miles, or about 990 statute miles.  
</P>
<P>
	Amenities: Models can include woodgrain cabinet with a beverage  
cooler, cup holders, flight manual storage and a pull-out Corian 
executive writing table, with provisions for an AM-FM CD stereo, 
flight phone, lap top computer workstation with fax-modem 
capabilities and multimedia entertainment center with videocassette 
player and LCD viewing panel. 
</P>
<P>
	Cost: About $325,000 to $350,000  
</P>
<P>
	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	Source: The New Piper Aircraft Inc., company Web site  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
