<HEADLINE> 49ers Give Receiver Owens 7-Yr Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Wide receiver Terrell Owens has reached a  
7-year contract agreement with the San Francisco 49ers worth at 
least $23 million, the San Francisco Chronicle reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The contract includes a signing bonus of $7.5 million and an  
escalator clause that could push the total value of the deal to as 
much as $35 million, the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement was approved Friday by the NFL's Management  
Council. The 49ers and Owens scheduled a press conference for 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, Owens had 67 receptions for 1,097 yards and 14  
touchdowns, including a 79-yard scoring catch. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, he had signed a one-year, $3.5 million contract,  
which counted against the team's salary cap. The new agreement 
spreads the economic impact over several years. 
  	   	
</P>
