<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Farrakhan Says Health Is Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Nation of Islam leader Louis Farrakhan said  
Saturday night that he is nearly rid of cancer and recovering from 
an ulcer caused by radiation treatments. 
</P>
<P>
	Speaking by telephone intercom to an audience gathered at a  
restaurant to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the Nation of 
Islam's newspaper, the Final Call, Farrakhan sounded upbeat during 
his 15-minute address. 
</P>
<P>
	``I believe within the next few months that ulcer will be  
completely healed and that your brother will be back with you,'' he 
said. ``I'm not an old man and I'm certainly not tired.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Farrakhan, 66, who was first diagnosed with prostate cancer in  
1991, underwent surgery March 30 to correct an inflammation caused 
by his treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	Nation of Islam officials would only say Farrakhan was speaking  
from one of his homes, but would not say which one. Farrakhan has 
at least two homes, one in Chicago and one in Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	Farrakhan explained that the ulcer led to very serious bleeding.  
``But by the grace of God, we caught it in time.'' He said he 
recently visited his doctors, who told him that the ulcer was 50 
percent healed. 
</P>
<P>
	Farrakhan said he hopes to publish the newspaper, which he  
started in his cousin's Washington, D.C., apartment before moving 
it to Chicago, in Spanish, Arabic and French on the African 
continent. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
