<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Venura Not Running for White House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. CLOUD, Minn. (AP) -- Al Gore, George W. Bush, take heart --  
Gov. Jesse Ventura is not going to make a run for the White House 
in the year 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am not doing it,'' the former pro wrestler said Friday.  
``You got to do the job. I don't want to be president. I like being 
the governor of Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	``Do you want to know who started all that? The media,'' Ventura  
said during a radio show appearance. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura didn't talk much about his upcoming return to the World  
Wrestling Federation ring as a referee. But he did remark that he 
liked the raucous wrestling crowd who showed up for the 
announcement Wednesday because they shouted down reporters who 
asked questions he didn't like. 
</P>
<P>
	The governor said he would like to make those fans a fixture at  
his news conferences. 
</P>
<P>
	``Anything political, I'm bringing the WWF fans in for it,''  
Ventura said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
