<HEADLINE> Highway Renamed for Babyface </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- When Kenneth ``Babyface'' Edmonds goes back  
home to Indiana, he should have no trouble remembering one of its 
highways -- it's just been renamed after him. 
</P>
<P>
	Indiana Gov. Frank O'Bannon dedicated a 17-mile stretch of  
Interstate 65 through Indianapolis in honor of the 10-time Grammy 
award winner, who was born and reared here. The governor presented 
Edmonds with a commemorative sign marking the Kenneth ``Babyface'' 
Edmonds Highway on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Kenny Edmonds has made great strides in the entertainment  
industry and has brought great distinction to the state of Indiana 
through his music and by never forgetting to give back to the 
community,'' O'Bannon said. 
</P>
<P>
	Edmonds is a singer, songwriter, and also a producer who has  
devised hits for artists ranging from Madonna to Toni Braxton. 
</P>
<P>
	Edmonds, 41, also produced the 1997 movie ``Soul Food.'' Vivica  
Fox, one of the movie's stars and a fellow Hoosier, served as 
master of ceremonies for Friday's ceremony. 
  	   	
</P>
