<HEADLINE> 'Felicity' Co-Star Not Angst-Ridden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Amy Jo Johnson says she's nothing like the  
angst-ridden best friend that she portrays on WB's teen show 
``Felicity.'' In real life, she's carefree. 
</P>
<P>
	The 26-year-old sings on the new Felicity soundtrack and, on  
Aug. 15, stars in VH1's ``Sweetwater,'' about a 1960s-era band. 
</P>
<P>
	The work is a fair distance from her past role as the pink Power  
Ranger. She says she had to prove herself to casting directors 
after that role. 
</P>
<P>
	``But it was good for me. I started studying harder,'' she says  
in the July 23 issue of USA Magazine. 
  	   	
