<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Avalanche Trade Backup Goalie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- The Colorado Avalanche traded backup goaltender  
Craig Billington to the Washington Capitals for future 
considerations on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Billington, 32, will go from backing up Patrick Roy to being the  
No. 2 goalie behind Olaf Kolzig in Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Billington compiled a 30-23-7 record with a 2.61 goals-against  
average and two shutouts during three years with the Avalanche. He 
went 11-8-1 with a 2.87 goals-against average last season. 
  	   	
</P>
