<HEADLINE>  McGwire Leaves After Strikeout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire struck out to end the first inning  
Saturday, then left the St. Louis Cardinals' game against the 
Chicago White Sox with tightness in his lower back. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire had two homers, his 30th and 31st, and had six RBIs on  
Friday night. He was replaced at first base by Shawon Dunston as a 
precautionary measure. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has missed only three starts and this was the second  
time he was removed due to an injury. He hurt his hamstring in 
Milwaukee April 20, then sat out one game. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire was batting .268 with 79 RBIs.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
