<HEADLINE> Plane Debris Found on Mass. Beach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AQUINNAH, Mass. (AP) -- An intensive search was under way today  
along the Atlantic seaboard for a small plane carrying John F. 
Kennedy Jr. to a family wedding in Massachusetts, the Coast Guard 
said. The only son of the nation's 35th president was traveling 
with his wife and his sister-in-law. 
</P>
<P>
	Hours after the search began, Coast Guard Lt. Craig Jaramillo  
confirmed the discovery on Philbin Beach on Martha's Vineyard, of 
``some luggage,'' a wheel, headrest and part of a plane support 
known as a strut. 
</P>
<P>
	He would not confirm reports that the luggage contained items  
with the name of Lauren Bessette, Kennedy's sister-in-law, who was 
reportedly aboard the aircraft. 
  	   	
</P>
