<HEADLINE> TBS to Launch 2nd Cartoon Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Turner Broadcasting System will launch a second  
cable television channel featuring 24-hours of cartoons beginning 
next spring. 
</P>
<P>
	The channel, to be called Boomerang, will go on the air April 1,  
2000, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Boomerang will mark a shift in strategy for the 7-year-old  
sister channel Cartoon Network. 
</P>
<P>
	Cartoon Network will focus on airing original cartoons.  
Boomerang will feature cartoons from the company's Hanna-Barbera 
library. 
</P>
<P>
	``Boomerang will serve baby boomers and kids ages 2 to 7,''  
Cartoon Network President Betty Cohen said. ``These people have 
told us they want more of the old Hanna-Barbera cartoons.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Cartoon Network will be marketed more to middle-graders,  
teens and young adults. 
  	   	
</P>
