<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico 2, Chile 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASUNCION, Paraguay, (AP) -- Miguel Zepeda's goal in the 87th  
minute gave Mexico a 2-1 victory over Chile on Saturday in the 
third-place game of the Copa America soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico opened the scoring in the 25th minute on a play crafted  
by attacker Luis Hernandez. He broke up the left side and fired a 
shot that goalie Marcelo Ramirez couldn't control. The rebound went 
out to Francisco Palencia, who tapped it in for a 1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico came out swarming in the second half, but it was Chile  
that scored the equalizer in the 80th minute. Raul Palacios stole 
the ball, worked a give-and-go with Jose Luis Sierra and eluded 
Mexican goalie Jorge Campos to make it 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
	With three minutes left, Hernandez set up the game winner,  
feeding Zepeda for the easy score. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
