<HEADLINE> Quotes by John F. Kennedy Jr. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Quotations from around the country Saturday about the  
disappearance of John F. Kennedy Jr.'s airplane: 

</P>
<P>
	``He has carried his legend with enormous grace and a commitment  
to live up to his father's legacy and his mother's love. ... One 
cannot help but reflect that the Kennedy family has given more to 
our country than any family should have to do. But our country is 
so much better because of the gifts that they have given. Our 
prayers are with the entire family this day.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Vice President Al Gore.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Our hearts go out to the Kennedy family. Goodness knows, this  
family has suffered enough tragedy. The thoughts and prayers of all 
the people of California are with the Kennedy family today.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- California Gov. Gray Davis.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a certain amount of disbelief. It brings back memories  
of the many tragedies of the Kennedy family. They've represented 
dreams, hopes for our whole country.'' -- Rep. Nick Lampson, 
D-Texas. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Nothing about our faith makes us pain-proof. It does hurt. It  
does make us cry. And we must dry our eyes and continue our work 
until our time is finished.'' -- the Rev. Jesse Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``When I first heard about it, I said, 'Oh no, not again.' The  
Kennedy family ... you talk about star-crossed. They've done a lot 
of good things, but, my gosh -- they've had a lot of tragedy in that 
family.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Sen. Tom Harkin, D-Iowa.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``On this particular day, our hearts go out to the family who  
has started so much, achieved so much, suffered and sacrificed so 
much and now has even further uncertainty.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Retired astronaut Buzz Aldrin, speaking at anniversary  
festivities for the Apollo 11 moon shot, which realized President 
John F. Kennedy's dream of putting a man on the moon. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``This is still a time of hope. My heartfelt thoughts and  
prayers and those of my family are with Caroline Kennedy 
Schlossberg, her family and the Bessette family at this difficult 
time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Tricia Nixon Cox, daughter of the late President Richard  
Nixon. 
  	   	
</P>
