<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Smooth Player Wins Hollywood Oaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Smooth Player beat favored Excellent  
Meeting by a half-length on Saturday in the $150,000 Hollywood Oaks 
at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye, the 13-1 longshot alternated on  
the early lead of the 1 1/8-mile stake, then withstood the closing bid 
of Excellent Meeting and jockey Kent Desormeaux while running the 
distance in 1:48. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2-5 favorite, Excellent Meeting was pinned along the rail  
turning for home, managing to break free at the eighth pole. By 
that time, however, Smooth Player was two lengths ahead and 
Excellent Meeting was unable to make up the deficit. 
</P>
<P>
	Nany's Sweep, who battled Smooth Player for the lead, wound up  
four lengths behind Excellent Meeting in third. 
</P>
<P>
	Smooth Player won $90,000, boosting her career earnings for  
owner John Spohler and Marty and Pam Wygod to $223,000. She has won 
five of eight starts, with one second and one third. 
</P>
<P>
	Smooth Player paid $29.80, $6.80, and $2.10. Excellent Meeting  
was worth $2.60 and $2.10 and Nany's Sweep returned $2.10 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Saturday, Tuzla won a three-quarter-length victory over  
Isle de France in the $70,400 Royal Heroine Stakes for fillies and 
mares aged 3 and up. 
</P>
<P>
	Tuzla ($3.40) went a mile in 1:34 1-5 and earned $42,240 for  
owner David Milch to bring her lifetime total to $734,247. She has 
won 11 of 18 starts, with three seconds and a third. 
</P>
<P>
	Isle de France finished two lengths ahead of pacesetter Chime  
After Chime. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
