<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Panderosa Wins Meadowlands Pace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- John Campbell won his fifth  
Meadowlands Pace, guiding The Panderosa to a stakes-record victory 
in the $1 million race on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Giving trainer Brett Pelling a great 41st birthday present, The  
Panderosa paced the mile in 1:49 3-5, taking 1-5 of a second off 
the stakes record set by Precious Bunny in 1991. It also equaled 
the track record shared by three other horses, including Nihilator. 
</P>
<P>
	The Panderosa not only won by 2 3/4 lengths, but overcame the  
outside No. 10 post position in winning for the fourth time in five 
starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think any other pacer could do what he did tonight,''  
Campbell said after winning his 18th million-dollar race. ``He is 
the greatest pacer I have ever driven at this point.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Panderosa paid $4.20, $3.20 and $2.20 and earned $500,000  
for Peter Pan Stables, owned by Robert Glazer. 
</P>
<P>
	Mystical Shark, making his fifth lifetime start, finished second  
and returned $4.80 and $3.20. Art's Conquest, winner of the New 
Jersey Classic, placed third and returned $4.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Goliath Bayama, who led the field entering the stretch, finished  
fourth and was followed by Grinfromeartoear, Badlands Hanover, 
Blissfull Hall, Washington VC, Sign of Success and Stutzpan, who 
was coupled in the wagering with The Panderosa. 
</P>
<P>
	Stutzpan, who broke from the No. 8 post with William O'Donnell,  
and Mystical Shark led the field of 10 3-year-olds through the 
first quarter in 26 1-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Campbell had moved The Panderosa into fourth place by that point  
and he had the winner of the North America Cup in third by the 
half-mile pole. 
</P>
<P>
	By that point, Goliath Bayama was on the lead and driver Sylvain  
Filion kept him there until Campbell attacked on the outside at the 
top of the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	Goliath Bayama stayed with The Panderosa for a few strides, but  
Campbell and his Western Hanover offspring found another gear and 
drew away. 
</P>
<P>
	Just before they got to the wire, Campbell thrust his whip up in  
the air in victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Mystical Shark angled off the rail to finish second but never  
challenged. 
</P>
<P>
	Campbell's other victories in the Meadowlands Pace were with  
Hilarion (1982), Dexter Nukes (1989), Cam's Card Shark (1994) and 
David's Pass (1995). 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
