<DOCNO> APW19990717.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-17 14:10:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clue on JFK Jr. Found in Remote Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AQUINNAH, Mass. (AP) -- Erin McCarthy and her friends felt safely  
away from the world as they frolicked about Philbin Beach on 
Martha's Vineyard Saturday, until they saw something in the water. 
</P>
<P>
	Their pulses raced, for they had heard on the radio that a plane  
carrying John F. Kennedy Jr. had disappeared on a flight toward the 
Vineyard. 
</P>
<P>
	A friend of McCarthy's, Damon Seligson, waded into the water and  
grabbed what turned out to be a piece of luggage. On the black 
suitcase was a Velcro-covered pouch. McCarthy and her friends 
peeled it back to see a business card. Lauren Bessette. 
</P>
<P>
	She is the sister of Carolyn Bessette Kennedy, the wife of JFK  
Jr. All three had been aboard the plane when it disappeared Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was kind of like, 'Oh God.' It seemed like it would be  
pretty bad news. Everyone was shaking,'' said McCarthy, 31. ``I 
think Damon almost had a heart attack.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McCarthy said she and her friends looked inside the bag and saw  
several items, including a bathing suit, a hairdryer and some 
makeup. 
</P>
<P>
	She and her friends called 911. Now the search for Kennedy that  
had extended from Fairfield, N.J. -- where he took off -- to Buzzards 
Bay off Cape Cod was focused. 
</P>
<P>
	Soon helicopters were hovering offshore, boats were searching  
the waters and swimmers and sunbathers were told to get off the 
beach. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was like mad pandemonium,'' said Mel Maddalene, a woman  
vacationing along the scenic beach that sits below sandy cliffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials closed Philbin Beach to the public about 2 p.m.,  
telling more than 200 sunbathers they might be in danger of getting 
cut by debris while swimming, said beach worker Will Codding, 17. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had no idea what was going when we came,'' said Katie  
Rossetti, 30, of Orange County, Calif. ``But now that I know, I'd 
be afraid to go in.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Kennedy was flying with his wife and her sister to Cape Cod for  
the wedding of Kennedy's cousin, Rory Kennedy, when the plane 
disappeared. 
</P>
<P>
	The search by late Saturday was focused near Philbin Beach at  
the edge of this community, which changed its name several years 
ago, although it is still most commonly known as Gay Head. 
</P>
<P>
	There are few houses in the area, which is covered by rolling  
hills of brambles and other scrub growth leading to sand cliffs and 
white beaches, which include a nearby lighthouse. 
</P>
<P>
	The beaches, remote as they are, were busy Saturday as  
temperatures were in the 90s. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were really looking forward to going to the beach. It's a  
beautiful day, but you just feel so bad. You just can't be angry,'' 
said Janine Rossetti. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
