<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Caddie Collapses at Ameritech  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONG GROVE, Ill. (AP) -- Two weeks after a caddie collapsed at  
another Chicago-area golf course, a caddie at the Ameritech Senior 
Open was taken to the hospital after experiencing chest pains 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The caddie, whose name was not released, was checked out by  
tournament medical personnel. Tournament spokesman Mike Brand said 
there were no signs of any problem, but added that the caddie was 
taken to Good Shepherd Hospital in nearby Barrington as a 
precaution. 
</P>
<P>
	Two weeks ago, Garland Dempsey collapsed and his heart stopped  
as he walked off the 15th tee at the Western Open. Paramedics had 
to use a defibrillator to get a pulse before he was loaded onto a 
stretcher and taken to a local hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	It's still not clear why Dempsey, 51, collapsed, but he had been  
taking medication for pancreatitis. Temperatures also were in the 
high 90s that day, with humidity making it feel over 100. 
</P>
<P>
	It was cloudy and cool on Saturday with periods of rain.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
