<HEADLINE> Dolphins Coach Marries Girlfriend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAVERNIER, Fla. (AP) -- Miami Dolphins coach Jimmy Johnson  
married longtime girlfriend Rhonda Rookmaaker on Saturday, 
fulfilling a commitment he made when he flirted with the idea of 
retirement earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The wedding took place in a private ceremony at an oceanfront  
home Johnson recently purchased in the Florida Keys. 
</P>
<P>
	It is the second marriage for both Johnson, who turned 56  
Friday, and Rookmaaker, 45. They met in 1984 while he was coaching 
the University of Miami and she was a hairdresser at a Coral Gables 
salon. 
</P>
<P>
	Five years later, Johnson split with his first wife shortly  
after being hired by the Dallas Cowboys. He awkwardly ended his 
marriage to the former Linda Kay Cooper after 26 years, telling 
reporters he no longer needed the social prop of a spouse. 
</P>
<P>
	Rookmaaker moved to Dallas shortly thereafter, and both returned  
to South Florida following his 1994 departure from the Cowboys 
after winning two Super Bowl titles. 
</P>
<P>
	After 15 years, the couple became engaged last January as a  
distraught Johnson nearly decided to retire from coaching. He 
disclosed their engagement at the news conference in which he was 
to announce his retirement, but suddenly decided to stay. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time, Johnson emphasized that the change of heart was  
only about retirement. 
</P>
<P>
	``The only thing she said was, `I'm not letting you off the  
hook. You're still marrying me,''' Johnson said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
